          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Bangladesh recalibrates
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/muhammad-yunus-invites-china-economic-expansion-bangladesh.png" alt="Bangladesh‚Äôs interim government chief adviser, Muhammad Yunus, has drawn attention by inviting China to expand its economic influence" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Bangladesh‚Äôs interim government chief adviser, Muhammad Yunus, has drawn attention by inviting China to expand its economic influence. Credits: News Arena India</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Bangladesh's interim government, led by Muhammad Yunus, received a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-04-2025-h1-1-red-carpet-welcome" target="_blank">red-carpet welcome</a> in China. This visit led to $2.1B in investments, loans, and grants. Important agreements include creating a Chinese Industrial Economic Zone, port upgrades, and more involvement in the Belt and Road Initiative.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          While China provides economic opportunities, worries remain about trade imbalances and the absence of social and environmental protections in its projects. Its relations with India were stronger under Sheikh Hasina but have since worsened due to nationalist rhetoric and actions against India, including inflammatory online actions and stamping the Indian national flag. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          India is wary of these changes. It sees Bangladesh's shift as a threat to its influence in the Bay of Bengal and security in its northeastern region. Tensions rise with Hasina's ongoing presence in India and reports of <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-04-2025-h1-2-violence-against-hindu-minorities" target="_blank">violence against Hindu minorities</a> under the current administration. With elections approaching in Bangladesh later this year, India may pause significant engagement and closely monitor the changing regional power dynamics.</p>
        </mj-text>
