        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Zelenskyy slams US</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/russian-missile-strike-damage-kryvyi-rih-ukraine-car-wreckage.png" alt="The shell of a car is part of the damage left after a Russian missile attack in Kryvyi Rih, Ukraine" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>The shell of a car is part of the damage left after a Russian missile attack in Kryvyi Rih, Ukraine. Credits: Governor of Dnipropetrovsk Regional Military Civil Administration Serhiy Lysak/Handout/Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">President Zelenskyy criticized the US for its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-04-2025-h2-3-weak-response" target="_blank">"weak" response</a> to a deadly Russian missile strike in his hometown, Kryvyi Rih. This attack killed 18 people, including nine children. The missile hit a residential area near a playground, and drone strikes followed during rescue efforts.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Zelenskyy reprimanded the US Embassy and Ambassador Bridget Brink for not explicitly naming Russia in a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-04-2025-h2-5-public-statement" target="_blank">public statement</a>. While Brink called the strike "horrifying," she did not identify the attacker. Zelenskyy complained that the word ‚ÄúRussian‚Äù was omitted from the statement. Ukrainian officials announced three days of mourning for the strikes.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Zelenskyy believes Russia is not seeking peace, pointing out the strike's location and timing during rescue efforts. Russia asserts it targeted a meeting of Ukrainian commanders and Western advisers. Meanwhile, Zelenskyy met with UK and French military leaders and remarked on "tangible progress" on <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-04-2025-h2-4-post-war-security-plans" target="_blank">post-war security plans</a>, though no further details were shared.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
