          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üá∂üá¶ More details on Qatargate: the scandal shaping Israeli politics </strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The "Qatargate" scandal is shaking up Israeli politics. PM Benjamin Netanyahu's top aides, Jonatan Urich and Eli Feldstein, are <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-04-2025-br1-9-accused-of-taking-payments" target="_blank">accused of taking payments</a> from Qatar to boost the Gulf state's image, especially as a mediator in the Israeli-Hamas conflict. This is seen as a contradiction as Qatar has been alleged to have funded the October 7, 2023, attack on Israel. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The investigation found misconduct and possible espionage. Both aides are alleged to have leaked classified information. Netanyahu has been questioned but remains officially untouched. He calls the scandal a political witch hunt. The scandal reveals how Middle Eastern states compete through information warfare, lobbying, and influence campaigns if proven true.</p>
        </mj-text>
