        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üá∫üá∏ Netanyahu to visit the White House</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu has finished his Hungarian visit and is set to meet with Trump in Washington. The leaders will <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-04-2025-br2-10-discuss-key-issues" target="_blank">discuss key issues</a> such as tariffs, the situation in Gaza, the Iranian threat, and the International Criminal Court (ICC). Netanyahu's visit follows Trump‚Äôs imposing a 17% tariff on Israeli imports. Despite Israel‚Äôs attempt to withdraw duties on some US goods, Trump went ahead with the tariffs, citing a significant trade deficit.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The tariffs could impact Israeli exports, including machinery and healthcare equipment. PM Netanyahu is the first foreign leader to address Trump directly in person over these tariffs. The trade tensions reflect a broader shift in US trade policy, contributing to global market instability.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
